  Justin Yochum, CFA | Selway Invest






























 












 

Navigation MenuMenu  
 
 



Justin Yochum, CFA 








ProfessionalsMark Matsko, CFAScott BrasseyJustin Yochum, CFADanielle Bugni, CFAJill Wilson 

 Vice President  & Portfolio Managert. 208.343.7556f. 208.343.5639E-mailV-Card Justin works with clients to help them achieve their long-term financial goals.  With dedication to their objectives, he manages the full life-cycle planning and execution for client portfolios.  Customization to particular needs is paramount, and he pays particular attention to risk tolerance and goal achievement.  Justin began his career at Selway in 2000 as an intern, was hired full time in 2006, and became partner in 2012.
Community Involvement
Justin is a member of CFA Society Idaho and Boise Young Professionals (BYP), and he volunteers at the Boise Rescue Mission.  He has a strong affinity for his alma mater, Boise State University, and he serves as a mentor to students in the business program.
Education, Licenses and Certifications
Justin received his B.A. in Accounting and Finance from Boise State University.  He also holds the professional designation of Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA).
Personal Interests
Justin’s favorite pastime is spending time with his wife and very active daughters.  Having lived in Idaho for nearly his entire life, Justin thoroughly enjoys the outdoor lifestyle the state offers.  Whether it is wakeboarding at the lake, golfing in the mountains, or taking weekend trips to the cabin in Featherville, being active is a way of life.



 
 
 
 

















  Mark Matsko, CFA | Selway Invest





























 












 

Navigation MenuMenu  
 
 



Mark Matsko, CFA 








ProfessionalsMark Matsko, CFAScott BrasseyJustin Yochum, CFADanielle Bugni, CFAJill Wilson 

 President and Chief Executive Officert. 208.343.7556f. 208.343.5639E-mailV-Card Mark joined Selway in 1996, and he has served as the President and Chief Executive Officer since October 2000.  His work experience includes general management, tax accounting, brokerage, portfolio management, and securities analysis.  Prior to joining Selway, Mark worked as a stockbroker in the Boise office of D.A. Davidson & Company from 1995-1996, and he managed Matsko Capital Management, a small private investment firm, from 1990 – 1995.
Before entering the investment business, Mark worked as a tax accountant in the Boise office of Arthur Andersen from 1981-1983, and held several positions with Coca Cola of Great Falls, Montana, including President, from 1983 until he negotiated the sale of that firm in 1986.  Mark was a private investor between 1987 and the formation of Matsko Capital Management in 1990, except for a brief period as a securities analyst with Growth Stock Outlook from 1989-1990.
Community Involvement
Mark is active in civic and social affairs in Boise.  He is a former Board Member of the United Way Treasure Valley, and he is the former director of the University of Montana Alumni Association.  Mark is also a member of the CFA Society Idaho.
Education, Licenses and Certifications
Mark was raised in Great Falls, Montana, and he graduated with High Honors with a B.S. in Accounting, Economics and Political Science from the University of Montana.  He holds the professional designation of Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA), and he is a former Certified Public Accountant (CPA).
Personal Interests
Mark enjoys spending time with his family and golfing at Crane Creek Country Club.



 
 
 
 

















